Rating: 3
Delicious salad though it could probably use about half the dressing. Next time I make this I am going to try to toss the zucchini slices with the salt FIRST and let it drain for a while, as it's not just a lot of dressing, but it gives off a lot of liquid. Otherwise delicious, and I would not omit the pine nuts nor the cheese - they add something special to the flavor. I found that this keeps well in the fridge too, but turns into more of a pickled consistency (which I don't mind).

